    "text": "Double homicide by setting fire to a house - Maharagama Police Division. Investigations have been initiated at the Maharagama Police Station on the evening of 18.01.2026, following a report that a house was on fire in the Pamunuwa area of the Maharagama Police Division. The fire was extinguished by residents of the area and a woman and a girl who were in a room on the upper floor of the house were found dead, while two people who sustained burn injuries were admitted to the Kalubowila Hospital for treatment. The deceased girl was 16 years old and the woman was 55 years old, a mother and daughter who were temporarily residing in the Maharagama area. It has been revealed that the deceased had been residing on a rental basis in the upper floor of this house, and one of the injured was the deceased woman's husband (46 years old). The other injured person is the 76-year-old owner of the house who lives on the ground floor of the house and it has been revealed during the investigation that he committed the arson.",
