  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      99.47,
      543.44,
      372.56
    ],
    "text": "A suspect who stole money and gold items after being given snacks and drinks has been arrested - Anuradhapura Police. On the night of 2026.04.02, three women who were travelling in a bus from Anuradhapura bus stand to Colombo for a short distance had eaten snacks and drunk a drink provided by an unknown person on the bus. At that time, the three women had fallen unconscious and investigations have been initiated on a complaint that the unknown person had stolen Rs. 17,06,400/= (one thousand seven hundred and six thousand four hundred) worth of money and gold items from the women and left. The suspect who committed this theft was arrested on the evening of 17.04.2026 in the Pandulagama area by a team of officers from the Anuradhapura Police Station. The suspect is a 54-year-old resident of the Saliyawewa area.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      387.14,
      543.29,
      485.19
    ],
    "text": "When the public travels by public transport, they sometimes offer snacks and drinks containing intoxicants based on the friendships they form with unknown persons. The police have previously warned the public on several occasions to be very careful and intelligent when accepting food or drinks offered by such unknown persons and the police further request the public not to fall prey to such fraudulent individuals.",
    "fonts": [
      "Kavivanar-Regular",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0,
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
